tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Finished T124 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournamentl in December...Three-year PGA TOUR Canada member earned first top-10 finish of the season with a T7 at the Staal Foundation Open, posting rounds of 67-71 on the weekend. Finish was eighth top-10 in 23 career starts...Finished T23 at the Nova Scotia Open, his first Web.com Tour start. Opened with a 2-over 73 then enjoyed three consecutive par-or-better rounds. The top-25 finish earned him a start in the Utah Championship the following week, where he missed the cut outside Salt Lake City...Rounds of 67-67-67-65 led to a T4 finish at the ATB Financial Classic for second top-10 finish of the PGA TOUR Canada season...Third top-10 was a T5 at The Great Waterway Classic in seventh start. Enjoyed four rounds in the 60s to finish four shots behind champion David Bradshaw...Finished 33rd on the Order of Merit.

2013: Finished solo third at the Syncrude Boreal Open presented by AECON in defense of his 2012 title...Posted three other top-10s. Was T8 at the Times Colonist Island Savings Open...Added a T10 at The Great Waterway Classic...Final top-10 of the season was a T6 at The Wildfire Invitational presented by PC Financial...Was 15th on final Order of Merit.

2012: Won the Syncrude Boreal Open presented by AECON, defeating Matt Hill in a four-hole playoff after shooting a course-record 63 in the final round...Finished T2 at the Times Colonist Island Savings Open, shooting a final-round 68 in front of hometown fans but coming up short when Andrew Roque birdied his final seven holes to win by three...Shot a 12-under 59 at an All-American Tour event before finishing second...Finished third on the Order of Merit...Made his PGA TOUR debut, at the RBC Canadian Open. Consecutive rounds of 70 left him one stroke outside the cutline at Hamilton G&CC.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won NAIA Vikes Turkey Shootout in 2006 and 2008...Won Inland Cup NCAA WSU in 2006...Won the 2007 Cal Poly Invitational...Captured the NAIA Regional Championship in 2009 and the RCGA University Championship the same year...Was named NAIA first-team All-American in 2008...Won CJGA Nike Junior Championship, was Victoria Zone Player of the Year, a Mizuno All-Canadian Award winner and Junior Team Canada captain.
tourBios.personal: Attended Claremont Secondary in Victoria...If not a professional golfer, would like to be a Division I golf coach...Earliest golf memory was a hole-in-one at age 12, using a 5-iron from 145 yards...First-tee intro song would be "Anaconda" by Nicki Minaj...Favorite courses he's played include Chambers Bay and St. Andrews' Old Course. Is a fan of the Seattle Seahawks and Vancouver Canucks. Watches "Suits", Seinfeld" and "Morning Drive." Is also a supporter of The Rock, "2 Guns", "Happy Gilmour" and "Wolf of Wall Street." Enjoys watching hockey players Sydney Crosby, Jonathan Toews and Steven Stamkos. Would visit and Las Vegas, Scottsdale and Cancun if he were going on vacation...Best sporting event attended is 2014 Waste Management Phoenix Open when he stopped by the Bird's Nest...Would like to trade places with Donald Trump for a day...Not many know he can dunk a basketball...Bucket list includes swimming with dolphins, sharks and whales...Twitter handle is @c_renfrew.
